    %>
    <p>There's a reason why meditation is so valuable.</p>
    <p>It's designed to take us out of character, and the more we practice this the more comfortable we can feel without them.</p>
    <p>Certainly, it's part of the reason why meditation can be so difficult, because it's asking us to essentially let go of everything we care about.</p>
    <p>And I would argue that most of the difficulty people face with their mental health comes down to a misunderstanding of what meditation is.</p>
    <p>When you're learning new skills and practices as part of mental health courses, what you're essentially doing is learning different ways to meditate and reflect.</p>
    <p>I suppose the issue I have is that I don't believe a lot of don't serve the purpose of mental health very well.</p>
